@title ClaimModule
 @author Set Protocol
 Module that enables managers to claim tokens from external protocols given to the Set as part of participating in
 incentivized activities of other protocols. The ClaimModule works in conjunction with ClaimAdapters, in which the 
 claimAdapterID / integrationNames are stored on the integration registry.
 
 Design:
 The ecosystem is coalescing around a few standards of how reward programs are created, using forks of popular
 contracts such as Synthetix's Mintr. Thus, the Claim architecture reflects a more functional vs external-protocol
 approach where an adapter with common functionality can be used across protocols. 
 Definitions:
 Reward Pool: A reward pool is a contract associated with an external protocol's reward. Examples of reward pools
   include the Curve sUSDV2 Gauge or the Synthetix iBTC StakingReward contract.
 Adapter: An adapter contains the logic and context for how a reward pool should be claimed - returning the requisite
   function signature. Examples of adapters include StakingRewardAdapter (for getting rewards from Synthetix-like
   reward contracts) and CurveClaimAdapter (for calling Curve Minter contract's mint function)
 ClaimSettings: A reward pool can be associated with multiple awards. For example, a Curve liquidity gauge can be
   associated with the CURVE_CLAIM adapter to claim CRV and CURVE_DIRECT adapter to claim BPT.
Throws if claim is confined to the manager and caller is not the manager

Design: The ecosystem is coalescing around a few standards of how reward programs are created, using forks of popular contracts such as Synthetix's Mintr. Thus, the Claim architecture reflects a more functional vs external-protocol approach where an adapter with common functionality can be used across protocols.  Definitions: Reward Pool: A reward pool is a contract associated with an external protocol's reward. Examples of reward pools   include the Curve sUSDV2 Gauge or the Synthetix iBTC StakingReward contract. Adapter: An adapter contains the logic and context for how a reward pool should be claimed - returning the requisite   function signature. Examples of adapters include StakingRewardAdapter (for getting rewards from Synthetix-like   reward contracts) and CurveClaimAdapter (for calling Curve Minter contract's mint function) ClaimSettings: A reward pool can be associated with multiple awards. For example, a Curve liquidity gauge can be   associated with the CURVE_CLAIM adapter to claim CRV and CURVE_DIRECT adapter to claim BPT.

devdoc.title: ClaimModule

addClaim(address,address,string).notice: SET MANAGER ONLY. Adds a new claim integration for an existent rewardPool. If rewardPool doesn't have existing claims then rewardPool is added to rewardPoolLiost. The claim integration is associated to an adapter that provides the functionality to claim the rewards for a specific token.

batchAddClaim(address,address[],string[].notice: SET MANAGER ONLY. Adds a new rewardPool to the list to perform claims for the SetToken indicating the list of claim integrations. Each claim integration is associated to an adapter that provides the functionality to claim the rewards for a specific token.

batchClaim(address,address[],string[]).notice: Claims rewards on all the passed rewardPool/claim integration pairs. Callable only by manager unless manager has set anyoneClaim to true.

batchRemoveClaim(address,address[],strin.notice: SET MANAGER ONLY. Batch removes claims from SetToken's settings.

claim(address,address,string).notice: Claim the rewards available on the rewardPool for the specified claim integration. Callable only by manager unless manager has set anyoneClaim to true.

getRewardPoolClaims(address,address).notice: Get list of claim integration of the rewardPool for the SetToken.

getRewardPools(address).notice: Get list of rewardPools to perform claims for the SetToken.

getRewards(address,address,string).notice: Get the rewards available to be claimed by the claim integration on the rewardPool.

initialize(address,bool,address[],string.notice: SET MANAGER ONLY. Initializes this module to the SetToken.

isRewardPool(address,address).notice: Get boolean indicating if the rewardPool is in the list to perform claims for the SetToken.

isRewardPoolClaim(address,address,string.notice: Get boolean indicating if the adapter address of the claim integration is associated to the rewardPool.

removeClaim(address,address,string).notice: SET MANAGER ONLY. Removes a claim integration from an existent rewardPool. If no claim remains for reward pool then reward pool is removed from rewardPoolList.

removeModule().notice: Removes this module from the SetToken, via call by the SetToken.

updateAnyoneClaim(address).notice: SET MANAGER ONLY. Update whether manager allows other addresses to call claim.
